      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Gateway — Deep Diagnostics\n\nCovers metrics **not** shown on the other gateway boards: backend-only latency vs E2E overhead, per-backend routing decisions, error breakdown, tokens/s throughput, streaming chunk counts, and request/response payload sizes.\n\n- **Backend latency** = time inside the upstream only (excludes validation + auth + response normalisation). Subtract from E2E to isolate gateway overhead.\n- **Tokens/s** = `completion_tokens / backend_duration_s` per request — the key throughput metric for comparing engine configs.\n- **Backend selection** = which backend was chosen and why (`model_match` vs `default_fallback`). High `default_fallback` means clients are sending wrong model names.\n- **Streaming chunks** = SSE data chunks forwarded per streaming request. High chunk count with low completion tokens → backend sending tiny chunks (inefficient).\n- **Payload sizes** = bytes sent to backend / bytes returned to client, useful for correlating latency with prompt length.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How to read this board",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
